From Andrew Patrick Subject Any Interest in a Mailing List on Epilepsy and Seizures I have seen a fair bit of traffic recently concerning Epilepsy and I am also interested in this subject I have a son with Epilepsy and I am very active with the local I posted a message like this a few months ago and received no replies but here it is Is anyone interested in participating in a mailing list on Epilepsy and seizures This would allow us to hold discussions and share information via electronic I already run a Listserver for two other groups so the mechanics would be If you are interested mail me a If I get enough replies I will make it happen and provide you with the BTW I have also started a database on This is part of my research on natural language question answering Users of this service are able to ask questions about Epilepsy and the program searches the database and retrieves its best The technology works by comparing your question against a set of questions that have been seen All new questions that are not answered are recorded and used to improve the This database is still small and sparse but we are adding new To try it out do the following telnet login chat Then select the Epilepsy item from the menu of Andrew Patrick Communications Research Centre Ottawa CANADA For a good time run telnet and login as chat